<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_action_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_action_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_action_assignment">
<p>A Required_resource_action_assignment is an association of a resource requirement statement with an action. 
The resource requirement statement could be related to many different types of actions such as:
task, task step, activity, activity method, etc.
</p>
<p>The role of the assignment is determined by classification.</p>
<note number="1">
The assignment can be classified as "Required_by", "Requires", etc.
</note>
<example number="1">A resource required by the activity "12" needs to be calibrated prior to usage. 
This calibration activity "21" is associated with the same required resource using another 
Required_resource_action_assignment.</example>
<example number="2">A resource required by the task "123" needs to be disposed after its usage. 
This disposal task "321" is associated with the same required resource using another 
Required_resource_action_assignment.</example>
</ext_description>
